[[ja:温泉神社 (別府市青山町)]] [[sn:Onsen Shrine (Beppu)]]

'''Onsen Shrine''' (温泉神社) is a {{ill|Shinto Shrine|ja|神社|12=draft|12=draft}} that once stood in Aoyama-chō, {{ill|Beppu City|ja|別府市|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Oita Prefecture|ja|大分県|12=draft|12=draft}}. It served as the guardian deity of one of the {{ill|Beppu Onsen|ja|別府温泉|lt=Beppu Hachiyu|lt_ja=別府八湯|12=draft|12=draft}}’s {{ill|Beppu Onsen|ja|別府温泉#別府温泉|lt=Beppu Onsen|lt_ja=別府温泉|12=draft|12=draft}}, and after {{ill|World War II|ja|第二次世界大戦|12=draft|12=draft}}, it was enshrined together at the {{ill|Hachiman Asami Shrine|ja|八幡朝見神社|12=draft|12=draft}}, with the rites of Onsen Shrine continuing there.<ref name="about">{{Cite web|和書 |url=http://www.asami.or.jp/about.php |title=朝見神社について |publisher=八幡朝見神社 |accessdate=2018-07-23 }}</ref><ref name="oita-press_2018-07-20">{{cite news |url=http://www.oita-press.co.jp/1010000000/2018/07/20/JD0057123337 |title=温泉神社の意外な事実 かつての社殿は春日神社に |newspaper=大分合同新聞 |date=2018-07-20 }}</ref>.
The Onsen Shrine located in Tetsuwan, {{ill|Beppu City|ja|別府市|12=draft|12=draft}} is not directly related to the Onsen Shrine (guardian deity of Tetsuwan Onsen) {{ill|Onsen Shrine|ja|温泉神社 (別府市鉄輪)|lt=Onsen Shrine|lt_ja=温泉神社|12=draft|12=draft}}.
