'''Onsen Shrine''' (温泉神社) is a {{ill|Shinto Shrine|ja|神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinto Shrine|qq=}} that once stood in Aoyama-chō, {{ill|Beppu City|ja|別府市|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Beppu City|qq=}}, {{ill|Oita Prefecture|ja|大分県|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Oita Prefecture|qq=}}. It served as the guardian deity of one of the {{ill|Beppu Onsen|ja|別府温泉|lt=Beppu Hachiyu|lt_ja=別府八湯|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Beppu Onsen|qq=}}’s {{ill|Beppu Onsen|ja|別府温泉#別府温泉|lt=Beppu Onsen|lt_ja=別府温泉|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Beppu Onsen|qq=}}, and after {{ill|World War II|ja|第二次世界大戦|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/World War II|qq=}}, it was enshrined together at the {{ill|Hachiman Asami Shrine|ja|八幡朝見神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hachiman Asami Shrine|qq=}}, with the rites of Onsen Shrine continuing there.<ref name="about">{{Cite web|和書 |url=http://www.asami.or.jp/about.php |title=朝見神社について |publisher=八幡朝見神社 |accessdate=2018-07-23 }}</ref><ref name="oita-press_2018-07-20">{{cite news |url=http://www.oita-press.co.jp/1010000000/2018/07/20/JD0057123337 |title=温泉神社の意外な事実 かつての社殿は春日神社に |newspaper=大分合同新聞 |date=2018-07-20 }}</ref>.
