'''Onsen Shrine''' (温泉神社) is a [[:en:Shinto shrine|Shinto Shrine]] that once stood in Aoyama-chō, [[:en:Beppu|Beppu City]], [[:en:Ōita Prefecture|Oita Prefecture]]. It served as the guardian deity of one of the [[:en:Beppu Onsen|Beppu Hachiyu]]’s {{ill|Beppu Onsen|ja|別府温泉#別府温泉|lt=Beppu Onsen|lt_ja=別府温泉|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Beppu Onsen|qq=}}, and after [[:en:World War II|World War II]], it was enshrined together at the {{ill|Hachiman Asami Shrine|ja|八幡朝見神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hachiman Asami Shrine|qq=}}, with the rites of Onsen Shrine continuing there.<ref name="about">{{Cite web|和書 |url=http://www.asami.or.jp/about.php |title=朝見神社について |publisher=八幡朝見神社 |accessdate=2018-07-23 }}</ref><ref name="oita-press_2018-07-20">{{cite news |url=http://www.oita-press.co.jp/1010000000/2018/07/20/JD0057123337 |title=温泉神社の意外な事実 かつての社殿は春日神社に |newspaper=大分合同新聞 |date=2018-07-20 }}</ref>.
The Onsen Shrine located in Tetsuwan, [[:en:Beppu|Beppu City]] is not directly related to the Onsen Shrine (guardian deity of Tetsuwan Onsen) {{ill|Onsen Shrines|lt=Onsen Shrines|lt=Onsen Shrine|ja|温泉神社 (別府市鉄輪)|lt=Onsen Shrines|lt=Onsen Shrine|lt_ja=温泉神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Onsen Shrine|qq=}}.
