Furthermore, the shrine building dismantled after the merger was relocated to Kasuga Shrine in Seikechō, [[:en:Ōita (city)|Oita City]] – the building having been lost in the {{ill|Oita Air Raid|ja|大分空襲|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Oita Air Raid|qq=}} in July [[:en:1945|1945]] (Shōwa 20) – and was used as its main hall. After a new main hall was constructed for Kasuga Shrine in [[:en:1967|1967]], the former building has served as a storehouse for the mikoshi.<ref name="oita-press_2018-07-20" />
